{"type":"message","id":"a31f66b3","parentId":"8fe0a92d","timestamp":"2026-04-10T09:25:26.374Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user has confirmed:\n- B (structured format with sections)\n- D (only send when there are actual changes)\n\nSo the Morning Report will be:\n- Structured with sections\n- Only sent when there are changes to report (no \"everything is fine\" spam)\n\nNow I should continue with the next question or summarize what we've established so far. Let me think about what else needs to be clarified...\n\nKey decisions made so far:\n1. Scope: Both human-readable AND LLM-optimized\n2. Migration strategy: Full migration (Option A) with backup\n3. Migration order: Hub-Notes first (C), then by relevance (A)\n4. Note structure: Template-based (D), hierarchical\n5. Semantic search: Hybrid (local + API) with agent deciding based on context\n6. Agent strategy: Config-driven (B) with smart-switch extension (A), user override (C), cost-tracking (D)\n7. Templates: Hierarchical (D) - Base types with specializations\n8. Storage: Balanced (B) - index + embeddings for active notes only\n9. Folder structure: Numbered with MOCs in each folder\n10. Date format: German DD-MM-YYYY\n11. Project structure: Hybrid (flat index files, attachments in subfolders)\n12. Naming: Snake_case\n13. Links: Aliases + folder-relative as fallback\n14. Night Agent: A+B+C+D (index, orphaned notes, duplicate detection, auto-summarize)\n15. Morning Report: Structured (B) + only when changes (D)\n\nWhat else should we clarify?\n- The actual first steps / implementation plan\n- Technical stack details\n- Integration with Obsidian\n- API key handling\n- Error handling for the Night Agent\n- Backup/versioning strategy\n\nLet me ask about the implementation approach - should we start with a manual migration of a few notes first to validate the structure, or build the Night Agent first, or something else?","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"**Entscheidung bestätigt:** Strukturierter Report, nur bei Änderungen.\n\n---\n\n**Frage 15 – Erste Schritte:**\n\nWie starten wir die Migration?\n\n- **Option A:** **Manuell** – Du und ich gehen 5-10 Beispiel-Notes aus dem Archive durch, erstellen Templates, validieren Struktur (langsam, aber lernt viel)\n- **Option B:** **Script-gestützt** – Ich schreibe ein PowerShell/Rust-Skript, das automatisch klassifiziert und migriert (schneller, aber fehleranfällig bei unstrukturiertem Input)\n- **Option C:** **Hybrid** – Manuell die ersten 10 Notes (Template-Validierung), dann Script für den Rest (Skalierung)\n- **Option D:** **Night Agent zuerst** – Agent bauen, dann durch das Archive laufen lassen (langsamer Start, aber sofort mit KI-Unterstützung)\n\n**Empfehlung:** Option C – Hybrid. Die ersten Notes manuell geben uns:\n1. Validated Templates\n2. Edge-Cases sichtbar\n3. Gefühl für die richtige Granularität\n\nDann das Skript für Skalierung.\n\nWas meinst du? Manuell starten oder direkt automatisieren?"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":29160,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":29160,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775813103467}}
