{"type":"message","id":"39b9dab7","parentId":"89b7055b","timestamp":"2026-04-10T13:00:40.896Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_mkm48RYCRFqsIW0mJ9EV2JL4","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#Requires -Version 5.1\n<#\n.SYNOPSIS\n    Backup/Restore Kommando für ECC Second Brain\n\n.DESCRIPTION\n    Erstellt und verwaltet Backups des ECC Second Brain Vaults.\n    Unterstützt ZIP-Kompression, Retention-Management und Verifizierung.\n\n.PARAMETER Action\n    Aktion: Backup, Restore, List, Clean, Verify\n\n.PARAMETER VaultPath\n    Pfad zum Vault\n\n.PARAMETER BackupPath\n    Pfad zum Backup-Verzeichnis\n\n.PARAMETER BackupName\n    Name des Backups (für Restore)\n\n.PARAMETER RetentionDays\n    Aufbewahrungsdauer in Tagen\n\n.EXAMPLE\n    .\\cmd-backup.ps1 -Action Backup\n    .\\cmd-backup.ps1 -Action Restore -BackupName \"backup_20260326_120000\"\n    .\\cmd-backup.ps1 -Action List\n\n.NOTES\n    Author: Andrew (andrew-main)\n    Version: 1.0.0\n    ECC Framework: Backup/Restore\n#>\n\n[CmdletBinding()]\nparam(\n    [Parameter(Mandatory = $false)]\n    [ValidateSet(\"Backup\", \"Restore\", \"List\", \"Clean\", \"Verify\")]\n    [string]$Action = \"Backup\",\n    \n    [Parameter(Mandatory = $false)]\n    [string]$VaultPath = \"C:\\Users\\andre\\Documents\\Andrew Openclaw\\SecondBrain\",\n    \n    [Parameter(Mandatory = $false)]\n    [string]$BackupPath = \"\",\n    \n    [Parameter(Mandatory = $false)]\n    [string]$BackupName = \"\",\n    \n    [Parameter(Mandatory = $false)]\n    [int]$RetentionDays = 30\n)\n\n# Script Variables\n$script:Version = \"1.0.0\"\n$script:StartTime = Get-Date\n\nif ([string]::IsNullOrEmpty($BackupPath)) {\n    $BackupPath = Join-Path $VaultPath \".backups\"\n}\n\n#region Functions\n\nfunction Write-BackupLog {\n    param(\n        [string]$Message,\n        [ValidateSet(\"INFO\", \"WARN\", \"ERROR\", \"SUCCESS\")]\n        [string]$Level = \"INFO\"\n    )\n    \n    $timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\n    $logEntry = \"[$timestamp] [$Level] $Message\"\n    \n    switch ($Level) {\n        \"INFO\"    { Write-Host $logEntry -ForegroundColor Cyan }\n        \"WARN\"    { Write-Host $logEntry -ForegroundColor Yellow }\n        \"ERROR\"   { Write-Host $logEntry -ForegroundColor Red }\n        \"SUCCESS\" { Write-Host $logEntry -ForegroundColor Green }\n    }\n\n[238 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775826040890}}
{"type":"message","id":"0e5522d5","parentId":"39b9dab7","timestamp":"2026-04-10T13:00:40.902Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_zzJzAPySaaZeAabD5TOUn1nA","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#Requires -Version 5.1\n<#\n.SYNOPSIS\n    Eval-Runner für ECC Second Brain CI/CD\n\n.DESCRIPTION\n    Führt Evaluierungen für das ECC Second Brain Framework durch.\n    Unterstützt YAML-Config, JSON-Output und Exit-Codes für CI/CD.\n\n.PARAMETER ConfigPath\n    Pfad zur Eval-Konfiguration\n\n.PARAMETER OutputPath\n    Pfad zum Output-Report\n\n.PARAMETER Suite\n    Spezifische Suite ausführen\n\n.EXAMPLE\n    .\\eval-runner.ps1\n    .\\eval-runner.ps1 -Suite \"Structure\"\n    .\\eval-runner.ps1 -OutputPath \".logs/eval-report.json\"\n\n.NOTES\n    Author: Andrew (andrew-main)\n    Version: 1.0.0\n    ECC Framework: CI/CD\n#>\n\n[CmdletBinding()]\nparam(\n    [Parameter(Mandatory = $false)]\n    [string]$ConfigPath = \"config/eval-template.yaml\",\n    \n    [Parameter(Mandatory = $false)]\n    [string]$OutputPath = \".logs/eval-report.json\",\n    \n    [Parameter(Mandatory = $false)]\n    [string]$Suite = \"\"\n)\n\n# Script Variables\n$script:Version = \"1.0.0\"\n$script:StartTime = Get-Date\n$script:Results = @{\n    version = $script:Version\n    timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"o\"\n    summary = @{\n        total = 0\n        passed = 0\n        failed = 0\n        skipped = 0\n        score = 0\n    }\n    suites = @()\n}\n\n#region Functions\n\nfunction Write-EvalLog {\n    param(\n        [string]$Message,\n        [ValidateSet(\"INFO\", \"WARN\", \"ERROR\", \"SUCCESS\", \"DEBUG\")]\n        [string]$Level = \"INFO\"\n    )\n    \n    $timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\n    $logEntry = \"[$timestamp] [$Level] $Message\"\n    \n    switch ($Level) {\n        \"INFO\"    { Write-Host $logEntry -ForegroundColor Cyan }\n        \"WARN\"    { Write-Host $logEntry -ForegroundColor Yellow }\n        \"ERROR\"   { Write-Host $logEntry -ForegroundColor Red }\n        \"SUCCESS\" { Write-Host $logEntry -ForegroundColor Green }\n        \"DEBUG\"   { Write-Verbose $logEntry }\n    }\n}\n\nfunction Import-EvalConfig {\n    param([string]$Path)\n\n[218 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775826040897}}
{"type":"message","id":"1ea2e025","parentId":"0e5522d5","timestamp":"2026-04-10T13:00:40.909Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"tool_wTfx9vUQZe78OVQKJuOxnxwM","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#Requires -Version 5.1\n<#\n.SYNOPSIS\n    Context Switch für ECC Second Brain\n\n.DESCRIPTION\n    Überwacht Token-Usage und führt Context-Komprimierung durch.\n    Unterstützt Session-Checkpointing und Smart Context-Compression.\n\n.PARAMETER VaultPath\n    Pfad zum Vault\n\n.PARAMETER ConfigPath\n    Pfad zur Config\n\n.PARAMETER CurrentUsage\n    Aktuelle Token-Usage in Prozent\n\n.PARAMETER Force\n    Context-Switch erzwingen\n\n.EXAMPLE\n    .\\context-switch.ps1 -CurrentUsage 85\n    .\\context-switch.ps1 -Force\n\n.NOTES\n    Author: Andrew (andrew-main)\n    Version: 1.0.0\n    ECC Framework: Stability\n#>\n\n[CmdletBinding()]\nparam(\n    [Parameter(Mandatory = $false)]\n    [string]$VaultPath = \"C:\\Users\\andre\\Documents\\Andrew Openclaw\\SecondBrain\",\n    \n    [Parameter(Mandatory = $false)]\n    [string]$ConfigPath = \"config/stability-config.yaml\",\n    \n    [Parameter(Mandatory = $false)]\n    [int]$CurrentUsage = 0,\n    \n    [Parameter(Mandatory = $false)]\n    [switch]$Force\n)\n\n# Script Variables\n$script:Version = \"1.0.0\"\n$script:Thresholds = @{\n    warning = 70\n    compression = 80\n    emergency = 90\n}\n\n#region Functions\n\nfunction Write-ContextLog {\n    param(\n        [string]$Message,\n        [ValidateSet(\"INFO\", \"WARN\", \"ERROR\", \"SUCCESS\")]\n        [string]$Level = \"INFO\"\n    )\n    \n    $timestamp = Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\"\n    $logEntry = \"[$timestamp] [$Level] $Message\"\n    \n    switch ($Level) {\n        \"INFO\"    { Write-Host $logEntry -ForegroundColor Cyan }\n        \"WARN\"    { Write-Host $logEntry -ForegroundColor Yellow }\n        \"ERROR\"   { Write-Host $logEntry -ForegroundColor Red }\n        \"SUCCESS\" { Write-Host $logEntry -ForegroundColor Green }\n    }\n}\n\nfunction Import-ContextConfig {\n    param([string]$Path)\n    \n    if (Test-Path $Path) {\n        # Load from YAML\n        return @{\n\n[167 more lines in file. Use offset=81 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1775826040903}}
{"type":"message","id":"8dc9a13f","parentId":"1ea2e025","timestamp":"2026-04-10T13:01:01.338Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Gute Analyse der 3 Scripts:\n\n1. **cmd-backup.ps1** (8,81 KB):\n   - Backup/Restore mit ZIP-Kompression\n   - Retention-Management (alte Backups löschen)\n   - Verifizierung\n   - Sehr nützlich!\n\n2. **eval-runner.ps1** (8,31 KB):\n   - CI/CD Evaluierung\n   - Test-Suites für Vault-Struktur\n   - JSON-Reports\n   - Nützlich für automatisierte Qualitätsprüfung\n\n3. **context-switch.ps1** (6,25 KB):\n   - Überwacht Token-Usage\n   - Context-Komprimierung bei hoher Auslastung\n   - Smart Compression\n   - Sehr nützlich für lange Sessions!\n\nAlle 3 sind wertvoll und sollten migriert werden.","thinkingSignature":""},{"type":"text","text":"## 📊 Analyse der 3 Scripts:\n\n| Script | Größe | Zweck | Nutzen | Empfehlung |\n|--------|-------|-------|--------|------------|\n| **cmd-backup.ps1** | 8,81 KB | Backup/Restore mit ZIP, Retention | 🟢 **HOCH** - Sichert Vault regelmäßig | ✅ MIGRIEREN |\n| **eval-runner.ps1** | 8,31 KB | CI/CD Tests, YAML-Config, Reports | 🟢 **HOCH** - Automatisierte Qualitätsprüfung | ✅ MIGRIEREN |\n| **context-switch.ps1** | 6,25 KB | Token-Usage Monitoring, Compression | 🟢 **HOCH** - Verhindert Context-Overflow | ✅ MIGRIEREN |\n\n---\n\n### Details:\n\n**1. cmd-backup.ps1** - Backup-Management\n```\nFunktionen:\n- Backup → ZIP-Archiv des Vaults\n- Restore → Aus Backup wiederherstellen  \n- List → Alle Backups anzeigen\n- Clean → Alte Backups löschen (Retention)\n- Verify → Backup-Integrität prüfen\n```\n→ **Sehr nützlich für Datensicherheit!**\n\n**2. eval-runner.ps1** - CI/CD Testing\n```\nFunktionen:\n- Vault-Struktur testen\n- YAML-Konfiguration validieren\n- JSON-Report generieren\n- Exit-Codes für Automatisierung\n```\n→ **Perfekt für Night Agent / automatische Prüfungen!**\n\n**3. context-switch.ps1** - Token-Management\n```\nFunktionen:\n- Überwacht Token-Usage (70% Warnung, 80% Kompression, 90% Emergency)\n- Context-Komprimierung bei hoher Auslastung\n- Session-Checkpointing\n```\n→ **Wichtig für lange Sessions mit vielen Tokens!**\n\n---\n\n## Meine Empfehlung:\n\n**Alle 3 Scripts migrieren!** Sie ergänzen unser System perfekt.\n\n**Soll ich:**\n- **A:** Alle 3 auf einmal migrieren (effizient)\n- **B:** Eines nach dem anderen (mit deinem GO dazwischen)\n- **C:** Zuerst nur das Wichtigste (cmd-backup), dann entscheiden\n\n**Was möchtest du?**"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"kimi-coding","model":"k2p5","usage":{"input":2108,"output":716,"cacheRead":157696,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":160520,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775826040917}}
